headline: AI could add $16T to the S&P 500, Morgan Stanley projects
summary: Artificial intelligence (AI) is expected to catalyze productivity gains and support economic growth. Morgan Stanley analysts say the emerging tech could add up to $16 trillion to the S&P 500's (^GSPC) market capitalization. Morgan Stanley global head of thematic research and sustainability research Stephen Byrd joins Market Domination to explain how the firm came to that estimate. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination.
